---
import PagePlate from "@/layouts/PagePlate.astro";
---

<PagePlate title="Privacy Policy">
  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto py-16 px-6 sm:px-8 text-gray-800 leading-relaxed">
    <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-center mb-8">Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="text-center text-gray-600 mb-12">Last updated: November 2025</p>

    <article class="space-y-8">

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-3">1. Introduction</h2>
        <p>
          At <strong>Tara G!</strong>, we respect your privacy. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and
          protect your information when you use our platform to explore or create trips. Our goal is to ensure transparency
          while keeping your experience safe and simple.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-3">2. Information We Collect</h2>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2">
          <li><strong>Basic Account Information</strong> – such as your name, email, and profile details provided upon registration.</li>
          <li><strong>Trip Data</strong> – titles, descriptions, and locations that you share publicly when creating or joining trips.</li>
          <li><strong>Usage Data</strong> – limited analytics data such as page views and interactions, used solely to improve site functionality.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-3">3. How We Use Your Information</h2>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2">
          <li>To operate and maintain the Tara G! community platform.</li>
          <li>To display user-generated trip content for discovery by other members.</li>
          <li>To communicate important updates, confirmations, or account notifications.</li>
          <li>To improve our website’s usability and performance.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-3">4. Data Sharing and Disclosure</h2>
        <p>
          Tara G! does <strong>not sell, rent, or trade</strong> your data to third parties. However, information you
          voluntarily share (like trip posts or comments) may be visible to other users as part of the community platform.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-3">5. Payment and Financial Data</h2>
        <p>
          Tara G! <strong>does not process or store any payment information.</strong> All trips and arrangements made
          between users occur independently and outside the platform. We are not responsible for transactions, cost-sharing,
          or disputes between users.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-3">6. Security</h2>
        <p>
          We implement reasonable security measures to protect your account and information. However, please note that
          no method of online data transmission is 100% secure. Always use caution when sharing personal information
          with others within the community.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-3">7. Your Choices and Rights</h2>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2">
          <li>You may access, update, or delete your account at any time.</li>
          <li>You may request removal of your personal data by contacting support.</li>
          <li>By using Tara G!, you consent to the collection and use of your data as outlined in this policy.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-3">8. External Links</h2>
        <p>
          Our website may contain links to third-party websites or external resources. Tara G! is not responsible for
          the privacy practices or content of these external sites.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-3">9. Changes to This Policy</h2>
        <p>
          Tara G! may update this Privacy Policy periodically. Continued use of the website after changes are published
          signifies your acceptance of the revised version.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-3">10. Contact Us</h2>
        <p>
          If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy or your data, please contact us at:<br />
          <strong>Email:</strong> privacy@tarag.ph
        </p>
      </section>

    </article>
  </section>
</PagePlate>
